Adult.description: American Tree Sparrows have a rufous stripe through the eye; on Chipping Sparrows it's black. Tree sparrows also have a spot in the middle of the breast and a bicolored bill that Chipping Sparrows don't have.
Field Sparrows have a bright-pink bill, a duller crown, and a distinct eyering; whereas Chipping Sparrows have a dull bill, a bright rusty crown, and a black eyeline instead of an eyering.
